results.name: a(n) is the largest number such that all of a(n)'s length-n substrings are distinct and divisible by 13.
example: a(2) is 9139 because its length-2 substrings (91, 13, 39) are all distinct and divisible by 13 and there is no larger number with this property
results.author: _Hans Havermann_, Mar 28 2004
